      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "@pinheadmz Ah, maybe we need different strings here. Instead of \"Verification progress\" maybe \"Validation progress\" in order not to confuse the two processes.\r\n\r\n\r\nLinux command: `ag \"Verification progress\"` gives (including the 100%):\r\n\r\n```\r\nbitcoin/test/functional/interface_bitcoin_cli.py\r\n184:        assert_equal(cli_get_info['Verification progress'], \"%.4f%%\" % (blockchain_info['verificationprogress'] * 100))\r\n\r\nbitcoin/src/validation.cpp\r\n4613:    LogPrintf(\"Verification progress: 0%%\\n\");\r\n4621:            LogPrintf(\"Verification progress: %d%%\\n\", percentageDone);\r\n4697:                LogPrintf(\"Verification progress: %d%%\\n\", percentageDone);\r\n4715:    LogPrintf(\"Verification progress: 100%%\\n\");\r\n\r\nbitcoin/src/bitcoin-cli.cpp\r\n1057:    result_string += strprintf(\"Verification progress: %s%.4f%%\\n\", ibd_progress_bar, ibd_progress * 100);\r\n```",
